# CareerLens — React + TypeScript Version

> AI-Powered Job-Specific Resume Analysis System
> Built with React, TypeScript, Vite, React Router DOM
> Subject: Advanced Web Technology (01CE1412) — Marwadi University B.Tech CE Year II

---

## Should I create a new folder?

**YES — 100% start fresh in a new folder.**

Do NOT mix the React version inside the old HTML/CSS project.
Keep them completely separate.

```
your-projects/
├── careerlens/              ← OLD project (keep this, it works)
│   ├── pages/
│   ├── css/
│   ├── js/
│   └── README.md
│
└── careerlens-react/        ← NEW project (React version, start here)
    ├── src/
    ├── public/
    ├── package.json
    └── README.md            ← this file
```

The old HTML project is your reference. The new React project is
your submission. Both can live side by side.

