## 4. Every File Explained

### src/main.tsx
The entry point. This is the first file that runs.
It mounts the React app into the single `<div id="root">` in index.html.
You never need to edit this file after setup.

### src/App.tsx
This is the router file. It lists every URL path and which page
component to show for that path. This replaces having 18 separate
HTML files. React Router reads the URL and shows the right component.

### src/context/AuthContext.tsx
This replaces our old `auth.js` file completely.
It stores the logged-in user, the JWT token, and exposes
login(), logout(), and register() functions to every component
in the app without passing props around.

### src/context/AnalysisContext.tsx
Stores the current analysis data (role, score, matched, missing)
so Results, Insights, Skills and Dashboard can all read it
without fetching it multiple times.

### src/components/shared/ProtectedRoute.tsx
This replaces the `requireAuth()` function in our old auth.js.
Wrap any page with this component and it automatically
redirects to /login if the user is not logged in.

### src/types/index.ts
All TypeScript interfaces live here.
Every piece of data has a defined shape — User, Analysis,
Notification, Settings, RoleSkill etc.
This is what satisfies the TypeScript requirement in the syllabus.

### src/utils/roleSkills.ts
The ROLE_SKILLS object from our old analyse.js — moved here
as a typed TypeScript constant so all components can import it.

