## 13. Syllabus Coverage

This project satisfies every practical in the AWT syllabus (01CE1412):

| Practical | Requirement | How CareerLens covers it |
|-----------|-------------|--------------------------|
| 1 | ES6+ syntax + TypeScript typing | All components use TypeScript interfaces and types |
| 2 | async/await + Promises + API calls | AI analysis fetch call, resume upload API |
| 3 | Multi-component React with props and state | Dashboard, Results, Skills — all use components |
| 4 | React form + validation + controlled components | Login, Register, Upload forms with useState |
| 5 | Routing + Context API state management | React Router + AuthContext + AnalysisContext |
| 6 | CRUD REST API backend | All 15 endpoints (Node.js + Express) |
| 7 | JWT auth + middleware | Login, ProtectedRoute, AuthContext |
| 8 | Real-time Socket.io | Loading screen progress events |
| 9 | TypeScript interfaces + generics | src/types/index.ts — all data typed |
| 10 | Node.js + Express + TypeScript backend | Backend project in TypeScript |
| 11 | SSR / performance (Next.js equiv.) | Code splitting via React Router lazy loading |
| 12 | Frontend + backend integration | All pages connected to backend API |
| 13 | Deploy to Vercel/Render | Netlify frontend + Railway backend |
| 14 | Mini full-stack project — React, Node, TypeScript | CareerLens is exactly this |

